The paper deals with approximation algorithms for graph problems, specifically Directed Multiway Cut and Node-weighted Multiway Cut. These problems are related to graph theory, algorithms, and optimization, which are all covered by various sub-categories in arXiv CS. The paper's focus on graph algorithms and optimization suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are likely sub-categories. The use of LP relaxations and multicommodity flow problems suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the investigation of lower bounds and integrality gaps suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as a possible sub-category.
